m%20watching%20culture%20clashes%20between%20colleagues%20from%20engineering%20and%20research%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20engineers%20often%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20agreed%20on%20an%20interface%2C%20I%20can%20implement%20it%20however%20I%20want.%26quot%3B%20Researchers%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20see%20the%20system%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20where%20even%20a%20tiny%20bug%20can%20quietly%20degrade%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20early%20project%2C%20Brockman%20said%20OpenAI's%20engineering%20team%20ground%20to%20a%20halt%20debating%20every%20line%20of%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20solution%20was%20simple.%20He'd%20propose%20five%20ideas%2C%20a%20researcher%20would%20reject%20four%2C%20and%20they'd%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20one%20that%20remained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20for%20engineers%2C%20Brockman%20said%2C%20is%20knowing%20when%20to%20trust%20your%20instincts%20and%20when%20to%20leave%20them%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20come%20in%2C%20really%20listen%2C%20and%20kind%20of%20assume%20that%20there's%20something%20that%20you're%20missing%20until%20you%20deeply%20understand%20the%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%2C%20at%20that%20point%2C%20great%2C%20make%20the%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrockman%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0389f87-7664-485f-9dcb-c3b2a8fe0d42%5C%22%3EWhat%20it%20takes%20to%20succeed%20at%20OpenAI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELeaders%20at%20OpenAI%20have%20spoken%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20for%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-employee-job-advice-nick-turley-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethrive%20at%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApproaching%20each%20scenario%20from%20scratch%20is%20so%20important%20in%20this%20space%2C%26quot%3B%