%20the%20amount%20of%20work%20that%20we're%20actually%20used%20to.%20This%20is%20not%20very%20sustainable%20because%20you%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20manpower%20needed%20to%20deal%20with%20things%20by%2010%20to%2020%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20AI%20will%20need%20to%20come%20in%2C%20allowing%20us%20to%20do%20more%20with%20less%20and%20deal%20with%20more%20parameters%20without%20increasing%20the%20amount%20of%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20could%20highlight%20areas%20of%20interest%20more%20quickly%20than%20we%20might%20examine%20under%20high%20magnification%2C%20improving%20both%20confidence%20and%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290e29e02-b1d7-405c-b8e2-066de63f1106%5C%22%3EAI%20has%20been%20part%20of%20pathology%20for%20years%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20involved%20in%20medical%20informatics%20for%20more%20than%20twenty%20years%2C%20starting%20when%20I%20was%20a%20medical%20officer%20in%20the%20Singapore%20Armed%20Forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20exposed%20to%20machine%20learning-based%20tools%20for%20digital%20pathology%20images%20about%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20project%20between%20Singapore%20General%20Hospital%20and%20AI%20Singapore%20from%202020%20to%202021%20focused%20on%20using%20AI%20to%20differentiate%20a%20tumor%20called%20fibroepithelial%20lesions.%20These%20aren't%20your%20traditional%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreast-cancer-signs-symptoms-lump-nipple-discharge-pain-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreast%20cancers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20rather%20two%20related%20conditions%20that%20can%20sometimes%20mimic%20each%20other%3A%20fibroadenomas%20and%20phyllodes%20tumors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20built%20AI%20algorithms%20to%20attempt%20to%20differentiate%20between%20these%20two%20lesions%20on%20biopsy%20materials.%20The%20goal%20was%20to%20improve%20our%20diagnostic%20confidence%20and%20better%20guide%20treatment%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a7036b5-3238-4d76-878d-b6d500c4be1b%5C%22%3EAI%20isn't%20infallible%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20complex%20cases%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20best-trained%20AI%20will%20have%20a%20margin%20of%20error%2C%20and%20its%20performance%20depends%20heavily%20on%20input%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20still%20has%20some%20way%20to%20go%20in%20integrating%20complex%20data%20to%20guide%20us%20to%20the%20correct%20diagnosis%20alongside%20what%20we%20see%20under%20the%20microscope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20we%20examine%20other%20data%2C%20such%20as%20patients'%20electronic%20records%20and%20radiology%20reports%2C%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20whole%20clinical%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20trained%20professionals%2C%20AI%20still%20has%20issues%20with%20adaptability%20and%20generalization%2C%20including%20dealing%20with%20issues%20in%20less-than-optimal%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20very%20dependent%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-data-source-solutions-openai-meta-google-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraining%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20AI%20encounters%20tissue%20that's%20been%20processed%20differently%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20samples%20from%20overseas%20labs%20that%20have%20different%20colors%20or%20appearances%20%E2%80%94%20it%20may%20perform%20suboptimally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20AI%20will%20mistake%20folded%20tissue%20on%20the%20slide%20as%20a%20positive%20finding%20when%20it%20shouldn't%20be.%20A%20trained%20human%20professional%20will%20be%20able%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20approach%20novel%20findings%20and%20situations%20they%20have%20less%20experience%20with%2C%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20force-fit%20into%20a%20category%20that%20AI%20may%20tend%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20human%20in%20the%20loop%20is%20inevitable.%20We%20always%20practice%20a%20margin%20of%20safety%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20don't%20make%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20many%20years%20of%20training%20helped%20us%20build%20the%20knowledge%20base%20that%20will%20allow%20us%20to%20make%20accurate%20interpretations%20and%20diagnoses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20time%2C%20AI%2C%20given%20enough%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-diagnosed-accurate-doctors-medicine-study-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20training%2C%20data%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20right%20guidance%2C%20may%20actually%20be%20able%20to%20do%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.nl%2Fbill-gates-says-ai-is-coming-for-2-kinds-of-jobs-that-once-seemed-tech-proof%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20will%20not%20replace%20doctors%20%3C%2Fa%3Eor%20humans%20in%20the%20medium%20to%20long%20term%2C%20a%20human%20without%20AI%20ability%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20rapidly%20evolving%20healthcare%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20will%20eventually%20transform%20the%20way%20we%20work.%20It%20will%20require%20us%20to%20acquire%20a%20different%20skill%20set%20and%20demand%20that%20we%20practice%20at%20a%20higher%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20AI%20in%20healthcare%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acmlee%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ecmlee%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajsmith%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3E.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-pathology-hospital-uses-cheng-chee-leong-help-patient-cases-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754870402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68512dff85e81483