amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc5yll33v9gwo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OpenAI's%20head%20of%20ChatGPT%20shares%20the%20one%20trait%20you%20need%20to%20be%20successful%20at%20the%20company%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225036%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20a%20computer%20with%20ChatGPT.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6897bcb0f748d8c055f735d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223777%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChatGPT%20just%20got%20a%20boost%20to%20its%20memory.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI's%20head%20of%20ChatGPT%20said%20it's%20those%20who%20can%20build%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20scratch%26quot%3B%20who%20succeed%20at%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENick%20Turley%20said%20the%20company%20looks%20for%20this%20quality%20in%20new%20hires%20and%20even%20tests%20for%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20critical%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20analogy%20for%20what%20we're%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-competition-big-tech-meta-talent-windsurf-amazon-movie-deepmind-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20job%20at%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20requires%20a%20strong%20tech%20background%2C%20experience%20at%20top-tier%20companies%2C%20and%20a%20genuine%20passion%20for%20AI%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESucceeding%20at%20the%20company%2C%20however%2C%20requires%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20without%20a%20playbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApproaching%20each%20scenario%20from%20scratch%20is%20so%20important%20in%20this%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Turley%2C%20the%20head%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Lenny%20Rachitsky%20on%20his%20weekly%20tech%20podcast%20on%20Saturday.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20analogy%20for%20what%20we're%20building.%20You%20can't%20copy%20an%20existing%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20OpenAI%20cannot%20iterate%20on%20products%20or%20features%20developed%20by%20existing%20tech%20giants%20like%20Instagram%2C%20Google%2C%20or%20a%20company%20already%20known%20for%20its%20productivity%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20learn%20from%20everywhere%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20do%20it%20from%20scratch.%20That's%20why%20that%20trait%20tends%20to%20make%20someone%20effective%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20it's%20something%20we%20test%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20an%20employee's%20ability%20to%20start%20a%20project%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurley%20also%20discussed%20OpenAI's%20release%20strategies.%20The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt5-free-chatgpt-openai-sam-altman-agi-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunveiled%20GPT-5%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%20to%20mixed%20reviews.%20He%20said%20OpenAI%20intentionally%20ships%20features%20before%20they're%20fully%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20crap%20for%20the%20model%20chooser%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20now-discontinued%20dropdown%20menu%20in%20ChatGPT%20that%20allowed%20users%20to%20select%20between%20OpenAI's%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurley's%20thesis%20is%20that%20it's%20better%20to%20%26quot%3Bship%20out%20something%20raw%20even%20if%20it%20makes%20less%20sense%26quot%3B%20so%20you%20can%20start%20learning%20from%20real%20users.%20Companies%20often%20wait%20to%20unveil%20products%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebecause%20they%20want%20to%20adhere%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20quality%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20actually%20better%20to%20roll%20out%20features%20quickly%20to%20ensure%20you%20get%20the%20feedback%20you%20need%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20really%20is%20that%20you're%20gonna%20be%20polishing%20the%20wrong%20things%20in%20this%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20won't%20know%20what%20to%20polish%20until%20after%20you%20ship%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20true%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20the%20properties%20of%20your%20product%20are%20emergent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20launch%20of%20GPT-5%20is%20an%20example%20of%20this%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ephilosophy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20criticism%2C%20the%20model%20switcher%20has%20been%20removed%20and%20replaced%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Breal-time%20router%26quot%3B%20that%20selects%20the%20most%20appropriate%20model%20to%20handle%20each%20user%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPreviously%2C%20you%20had%20to%20go%20deal%20with%20the%20model%20picker%20in%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt-5-model-switching-best-for-average-user-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20COO%20Brad%20Lightcap%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Big%20Technology%2C%20a%20tech%20newsletter%2C%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BYou%20had%20to%20select%20a%20model%20that%20you%20wanted%20to%20use%20for%20a%20given%20task.%20And%20then%20you'd%20run%20the%20process%20of%20asking%20a%20question%2C%20getting%20an%20answer.%20Sometimes%20you%20choose%20a%20thinking%20model%2C%20sometimes%20you%20wouldn't.%20And%20that%20was%2C%20I%20think%2C%20a%20confusing%20experience%20for%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20satisfy%20everyone.%20After%20GPT-5's%20release%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupgrade-chatgpt-5-met-with-frustration-tears-gpt4o-reddit-altman-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eusers%20immediately%20complained%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20could%20no%20longer%20access%20a%20fan-favorite%20older%20model.%20So%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altm