x%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gurusamy%20says%20the%20open%20land%20with%20greenery%20became%20a%20safe%20habitat%20with%20assured%20food%20for%20the%20deer.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123128.971-1754556152-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483125%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGurusamy%20says%20the%20open%20land%20with%20greenery%20became%20a%20safe%20habitat%20with%20assured%20food%20for%20the%20deer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20day%20in%201998%2C%20I%20saw%20three%20spotted%20deer%20grazing%20on%20grass%2C%20alongside%20my%20goats.%20I%20was%20amused%20by%20the%20sight%2C%20as%20the%20deer%20followed%20the%20cattle%20to%20feed%20on%20grass.%20To%20my%20surprise%2C%20they%20never%20really%20left%2C%20and%20instead%20became%20a%20frequent%20visitor%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurusamy%20believes%20that%20the%20deer%20ventured%20into%20his%20territory%20from%20the%20neighbouring%20Mettupalayam%20Forest%20of%20Western%20Ghats%20for%20water%20and%20food.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20region%20has%20been%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fstates%2Ftamil-nadu%2F2019%2Fmar%2F21%2F24-districts-declared-as-drought-hit-number-to-rise-in-coming-months-1953962.html%5C%22%3Edrought%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20shortage%20of%20rainfall%20for%20the%20past%2025%20years.%20River%20Khousikha%20used%20to%20have%20water%20for%20most%20of%20the%20year%2C%20but%20now%20runs%20dry.%20The%20groundwater%20table%20has%20also%20decreased%20owing%20to%20overexploitation%20of%20the%20water%20for%20irrigation.%20The%20deer%20must%20have%20faced%20the%20brunt%20of%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2070-year-old%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%2060%20acres%20of%20ancestral%20land%2C%20and%20during%20those%20days%2C%20practised%20organic%20farming%20over%2015%20acres%20of%20land%20growing%20corn%2C%20cotton%20and%20seasonal%20vegetables.%20I%20dedicated%20the%2045%20acres%20of%20land%20for%20my%20100%20cows%20and%20goats%20to%20graze%20and%20grow%20indigenous%20plants.%20I%20use%20the%20cow%20dung%20from%20the%20cattle%20for%20making%20organic%20fertiliser.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurusamy%20says%20the%20open%20land%20with%20greenery%20became%20a%20safe%20habitat%20with%20assured%20food%20for%20the%20deer.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20deer%20made%20the%20land%20home.%20I%20eventually%20limited%20my%20farming%20area%20to%2010%20acres%20and%20gave%20away%2050%20acres%20for%20animals%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20he%20felt%20compassion%20towards%20the%20deer%20and%20did%20not%20want%20to%20harm%20them%20or%20shoo%20them%20away.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20seen%20some%20instances%20of%20dogs%20attacking%20the%20deer%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20protect%20the%20wildlife.%20I%20realised%20that%20my%20farmland%20would%20keep%20the%20deer%20safe%2C%20away%20from%20outside%20threats%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20farmer%20says%20that%20of%20the%20three%20deer%2C%20one%20was%20male%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%20were%20female.%20As%20the%20animals%20started%20breeding%2C%20not%20everyone%20was%20kind%20enough%20to%20sympathise%20with%20the%20wild%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20deer%20population%20grew%20over%20the%20years%2C%20and%20no%20one%20knew%20about%20them%20until%202005.%20The%20numbers%20had%20increased%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20the%20deer%20started%20reaching%20nearby%20farms%20and%20often%20damaging%20the%20crops%20in%20the%20process.%20Other%20farmers%20felt%20threatened.%20Our%20village%20and%20neighbouring%20districts%20had%20a%20rainfall%20deficit%20around%20the%20mid-2000s.%20The%20deer%20walked%20into%20other%20farms%20to%20access%20water%20in%20their%20ponds%20and%20feed%20on%20the%20crops.%20Some%20complained%20to%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20district%20administration%20officials%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Considering%20the%20increasing%20threats%2C%20Gurusamy%20has%20requested%20authorities%20to%20relocate%20the%20deer%20to%20a%20safer%20place.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123213.673-1754556116-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483123%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EConsidering%20the%20increasing%20threats%2C%20Gurusamy%20has%20requested%20authorities%20to%20relocate%20the%20deer%20to%20a%20safer%20place.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20a%20local%20newspaper%20journalist%20found%20out%20about%20the%20ordeal%2C%20he%20wrote%20about%20the%20increasing%20wildlife%20in%20the%20area.%20Taking%20cue%20from%20the%20news%20article%2C%20urban%20dwellers%20started%20visiting%20the%20place%20to%20see%20the%20deer%2C%20Gurusamy%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Gurusamy%20has%20no%20complaints%20and%20understands%20the%20reason%20why%20farmers%20considered%20the%20deer%20a%20menace.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20already%20suffered%20from%20a%20shortage%20of%20water%2C%20and%20the%20production%20of%20crops%20was%20declining.%20The%20damage%20by%20the%20deer%20added%20to%20their%20losses%20and%20was%20not%20acceptable%20to%20them.%20Some%20adopted%20dogs%20to%20chase%20the%20deer%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20chasing%20away%20deer%20often%20scared%20them%2C%20and%20the%20wild%20animals%20ran%20helter-skelter%2C%20and%20some%20became%20victims%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FCoimbatore%2Fdeer-deaths-cause-concern%2Farticle18413282.ece%5C%22%3Eroad%20accidents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20deer%20population%20also%20attracted%20poachers%20who%20started%20hunting%20them%20for%20meat%20and%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGurusamy%20says%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20convince%20the%20farmers%2C%20but%20in%20vain.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20all%20went%20against%20me%20and%20reported%20it%20to%20the%20collector.%20I%20am%20struggling%20to%20create%20awareness%20and%20change%20their%20perception%20towards%20the%20animal%20to%20date.%20It%20is%20only%20my%20friend%20C%20Balasundaram%20who%20has%20always%20supported%20my%20cause.%20He%20allowed%20deer%20to%20wander%20in%20his%20coconut%20grove%20spread%20across%20several%20acres%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalasundram%20also%20helped%20Gurusamy%20catch%20two%20teams%20of%20poachers%20in%202008%20and%202010.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reported%20the%20issue%20to%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20have%20received%20constant%20support%20from%20the%20officials.%20They%20have%20promised%20us%2024%2F7%20assistance.%20To%20prevent%20the%20deer%20from%20venturing%20outside%2C%20I%20built%20a%20couple%20of%20ponds%20on%20the%20farm.%20The%20officials%20from%20the%20forest%20department%20fill%20the%20water%20during%20peak%20summer%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenthil%20Kumar%2C%20Range%20Forest%20Officer%2C%20Tirupur%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20population%20of%20deer%20has%20increased%20tremendously%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades.%20According%20to%20a%20census%20conducted%20in%20August%202021%2C%20the%20deer%20population%20stands%20around%201%2C800.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenthil%20says%20the%20department%20assists%20Gurusamy%20in%20protecting%20the%20deer%20and%20understand%20their%20needs.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20round%20the%20clock%20patrolling%20by%20forest%20guards%20to%20control%20poaching%20and%20illegal%20activities%20that%20may%20threaten%20the%20population%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20hunt%20for%20a%20safer%20place%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20some%20NGOs%20and%20environmentalists%20also%20started%20showing%20support%20to%20Gurusamy%20and%20his%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EK%20Ravindran%2C%20an%20environmentalist%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Nature%20Society%20of%20Tirupur%2C%20an%20NGO%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20following%20Gurusamy%E2%80%99s%20work%20since%202010%2C%20and%20his%20work%20is%20commendable%20in%20protecting%20and%20increasing%20the%20deer%20population.%20However%2C%20deer%20is%20a%20herbivorous%20species%2C%20and%20there%20are%20no%20carnivores%20to%20keep%20a%20tab%20on%20the%20grazing%20population%20in%20the%20surroundings.%20Moreover%2C%20with%20banana%2C%20tapioca%20and%20other%20dense%20tree%20plantations%2C%20one%20can%20mistake%20Gurusamy%E2%80%99s%20farm%20for%20a%20mini%20forest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%20The%20district%20collector%20and%20forest%20department%20officials%20frequently%20visit%20the%20farm%20to%20ensure%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20wildlife.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T123147.373-1754556071-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483121%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20district%20collector%20and%20forest%20department%20officials%20frequently%20visit%20the%20farm%20to%20ensure%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20wildlife.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavindran%20says%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20predators%20has%20led%20to%20an%20exploding%20population%20of%20deer.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20classic%20example%20of%20how%20a%20fragmented%20forest%20can%20lead%20to%20an%20imbalance%20in%20the%20ecosystem%20and%20disturb%20the%20food%20chain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20about%20110%20deer%20during%20my%20first%20visit%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20and%20today%20there%20are%20hundreds%20thriving%20in%20the%20area.%20The%20district%20collector%20and%20forest%20department%20officials%20frequently%20visit%20the%20farm%20to%20ensure%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20wildlife.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20increasing%20threats%2C%20Gurusamy%20has%20requested%20authorities%20to%20relocate%20the%20deer%20to%20a%20safer%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEchoing%20Gurusamy%E2%80%99s%20same%20thoughts%2C%20Ravindran%20says%20that%20relocation%20of%20the%20deer%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%2C%20but%20has%20its%20own%20challenges.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20deer%20is%20a%20sensitive%20animal.%20Even%20a%20shock%20or%20long%20chase%20can%20lead%20to%20tiredness%20and%20can%20result%20in%20death.%20Tranquillisation%20of%20the%20animal%20and%20relocating%2C%20a%20common%20practice%20with%20predators%2C%20will%20not%20serve%20as%20a%20feasible%20alternative.%20The%20relocation%20will%20require%20a%20slow%20and%20long%20term%20plan%2C%20and%20we%20are%20exploring%20solutions%20to%20suggest%20to%20the%20officials%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ravindran%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20uncertain%20future%20for%20the%20deer%2C%20Gurusamy%20says%20that%20he%20will%20continue%20to%20protect%20the%20wildlife.%20%E2%80%9CI%20do%20not%20need%20any%20support%20and%20will%20fight%20with%20the%20farmers%20for%20the%20deer%E2%80%99s%20safety.%20The%20state%20government%20has%20sanctioned%20an%20irrigation%20pipeline%20to%20address%20the%20water%20woes%20for%20the%20farmers.%20Access%20to%20water%20may%20increase%20threats%20for%20deer%2C%20and%20hence%20an%20urgent%20solution%20is%20needed%20to%20reduce%20conflict%20between%20humans%20and%